You can use the `functools.wraps` decorator to deal with copying all (most) metadata from the wrapped function:<p><pre><code>    def trace(fn):
        @functools.wraps(fn)
        def worker(*args):
            logging.info(&#x27;Called %s with args %r&#x27;, fn.__name__, args)
            return fn(*args)
        return worker
</code></pre>
